<TITLE> Former BFF stalwart dies at 59 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 13 (bdnews24.com) Former general secretary of the Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) Sheikh Akmal Hossain died of kidney failure Sunday morning at the Shikdar Medical Hospital in Gulshan. He was 59. Hossain, a former general secretary and life-time member of Mohammedan Sporting Club, had also suffered from breathing problems for some time. He is survived by his wife, two sons and a daughter. A Namaj-e-Janaja was held at the Old DOSH Mosque prior to his burial at Banani Graveyard. The BFF and Mohammedan Sporting Club expressed their deepest sympathy in separate statements addressed to the bereaved family and prayed for eternal peace of the departed soul. Mohammedan will fly its club flag at half-mast to mark the death of the club stalwart for three days. bd
